# AIJ Case C — Urban CFD Workflow

## Overview

This tutorial walks you through a complete CFD simulation of the **AIJ Case C** benchmark — a standard test case published by the Architectural Institute of Japan (AIJ) for validating pedestrian-level wind simulations around buildings.

**What is AIJ Case C?**

AIJ Case C represents a 3×3 array of low-rise buildings with a taller building at the center. It is widely used in the CFD community as a benchmark because wind tunnel experimental data is publicly available, making it possible to check how well a simulation reproduces real flow behaviour.

<!-- IMAGE: schematic top-view diagram of the 3×3 building array, showing the taller
