**What you will learn:**

- How to build a simple urban geometry in Blender and export it for CFD
- How to set up a RANS simulation in OpenFOAM 12 with realistic wind inlet conditions
- How to visualise and interpret the results in ParaView

**Tools required:**

| Tool | Purpose | Version |
|------|---------|---------|
| [Blender](https://www.blender.org/) | Geometry generation | 3.x or later |
| [OpenFOAM](https://openfoam.org/) | CFD solver | 12 |
| [ParaView](https://www.paraview.org/) | Post-processing | 5.x or later |

